<br>
Naming names, I recently got screwed over on raptors by a druid on Xegony named Ksuneo.  I spent levels 43-60 in TD so a lesson I learned early is that you must, you MUST communicate in that place or people die.  And unless you have a cleric twink or you're one heck of a cyber expert it's almost impossible to get a cleric out there for a res.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I was on large raptor island, as I had been for several hours that day.  Yes, I was doing all 8.  Another wizard was doing the other 7 raptors.  Ksuneo zones in and asks me and the other wizard if we're doing raptors.  We say yes, and we all agree he can have the single spawn on the north of big island until one of us leaves.  Ksuneo communicates that to me and it's all good, right?<br>
<br>
Wrong.  Well about this time our guildleader says it's time to head to Ssra temple.  I'm bound @mons lethalis, so I figure I have another 3 quads and I'm set.  Meanwhile, without even speaking to me, Ksuneo petitions me for taking all 8 raptors.  I didn't know it yet, but I received a tell from him saying that he wanted to make arrangements for him to take half of big island or did he need to petition me.  I'm thinking WTF, he's threatening to PNP me?  So that's what I asked him, was he planning on PNPing me.  I also expressed my shock to the other wizard at what was going on, and he pointed out the guide was already in the zone.<br>
<br>
Anyhow since I wanted to keep the spawns broken properly I asked the druid to hold on a sec and rounded up the 2 vicious and 2 raptors and killed them.  I came back to the camp spot and there was the druid and the guide.  The guide said that I was taking all the raptors (I had only taken these 4 since this started) and I needed to work something out with Ksuneo in says.  Throughout this he's sending me tells about how he doesn't want to call a gm (she was already there) and just give him 4 raptors.  Well I was planning on leaving anyhow so it was no big deal besides the annoyance.  Anyhow, I say to him if he wants to talk that's fine but does he really want to be known as a PNPer by involving a GM?<br>
<br>
Well the guide put a warning on my account for threatening Ksuneo.  The punk swore he didn't ask for it to happen.  I asked the guide how I'd threatened him after about five minutes of hemming and hawwing and she said that I had threatened him by telling him he'd be known as a PNPer.  That's a threat?  It's not like I mentioned he was going to get any kind of backlash at all.  I wanted him to dismiss the GM, that's all.  Well now I had a warning on my otherwise spotless account.  I have a pretty good reputation on my server, so this annoyed the living hell out of me.  To make a long story short, I asked for the matter to be escalated, she made me repetition for that, I did, the senior guide said it wasn't a big deal to have 1 warning on an account and just don't worry about it, Ksuneo got all 8 raptors, and I got to the guild raid 45 minutes late and missed rolling for Greater Familiar.<br>
<br>
So if you're on Xegony and you see this sack of crap, ask him how he feels being a PNPer, and unnecessarily getting a warning put on someone's account.  But don't use my name or I'm bound to get another warning <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR>
