<br>
I say bullshit.  Some people playing this game are real jerks or really immature kids, and many of them play druids.  Many of them started as wizards, but then quit them when they found out the class was hard (remember 2-3 years ago when Wiz = KSers?)<br>
<br>
Anyway, all I will add to this thread is if anyone thinks the druids in the stories above weren't trying to kill folks, you are kidding yourself.  They may have invented some BS story, or pleaded ignorance, but the truth is they were training to kill and eliminate competition for spawns.<br>
<br>
In particular, druids do this because they view wizards as competition and inferior competition to boot.  Why do I say this?  Because they can solo about twice as fast as us at most levels based on DOTs and the inherent efficiency of wis based casting.  <br>
<br>
So to them, not only are you (a wizard) taking their spawns, you aren't even killing fast enough to make the druid feel it's justified.  How's that for logic?  Now, before everyone goes bananas, understand that I don't think EVERY druid is a vile kiting rodent, just a good many of them are imho.  Some are truly helpful folks who just wanna play and have fun too.<br>
<br>
But my toon has been killed on purpose by PCs on four  occasions, three were out-and-out pixel murder (for certain) and once possibly by accident (but I have my suspicions).  In any event each time it was a druid.  And in one case the druid actually admitted my speed in taking down ice giants was an issue with him.  <br>
<br>
I started a druid on another server, simply becuase I wanted to get to the point where I could twink a few lowbies in a few months.  What can I say?  I ran out of slots and I like variety <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   So OK I'm a much more experienced player (aren't we all) and I probably am being very efficient in selecting where and what to hunt, but OMG the class is SO easy to play.  Basically once you hit sow level, you are a soloing machine.  So I agree with the other posts which indicate that druids, along with being a neat and well balanced class, are also the class of choice for the selfish powergamer types (can you say tracking?).<br>
<br>
Yeah it's not great to generalize, but if the paws fit...<br>
